HEADWORD: Nuptial
<hw>Nup"tial</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧p"sh⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nuptialis</ets>, fr. <ets>nuptiae</ets> marriage, wedding, fr.
<ets>nubere</ets>, <ets>nuptum</ets>, prop., to cover, to veil, hence,
to marry, as the head of the bride was covered with a veil; cf. Gr. <?/
bride, nymph: cf. F. <ets>nuptial</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to
marriage; done or used at a wedding; <as>as, <ex>nuptial</ex> rites and
ceremonies</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then, all in heat,⟦br⟧
